# ProjectFlo — Frontend Architecture

- All new frontend code must live under one of: `app` (routes only), `features` (domain behavior, UI, hooks, types, API bindings), or `shared` (cross-domain primitives). Do not create new top-level buckets under `packages/frontend/src`.
- Treat `src/lib/types/`, `src/types/`, `src/components/`, and `src/hooks/` as legacy-frozen: never add or move new code into these folders, and do not re-export new feature code from them.
- Every feature belongs to exactly one domain bucket under `features`: `platform`, `catalog`, `workflow`, `content`, or `finance`; do not invent new buckets like `sales` or `portal` at the `features` root.
- Route files in `app` (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, etc.) are thin shells: read params, call feature hooks/screens, and render — business logic, types, and API calls live in the owning feature.
- Each feature should follow the standard shape (`api/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, `screens/`, `types/`, `constants/`, `mappers/`, `selectors/`, `index.ts`) and keep feature-specific pieces colocated.
- Respect file size limits (routes, components, hooks, utilities); when a file exceeds its target/hard ceiling, split it before adding new logic and update the feature `README.md` to match the new structure.

